The course gives an overview of the essence, aims and principles of CLIL, considering the National Currriculum of Basic School and modern multicultural learning environment.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give students knowledge and skills enabling them to create and manage study process that integrates and values content knowledge, language skills, culture and cognition.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student *knows the aims, principles and key concepts of CLIL; *can make interdisciplinary connections, while developing students' content knowledge, language and study skills; *knows the tools to create a learning environment that supports active learning and develops learner autonomy; * knows how to use a cross-curricular approach, create suitable topic-related activities while choosing, adapting, and designing study materials for the CLIL classroom; *knows the assessment principles used in the CLIL classroom, can develop and implement CLIL-specific assessment tools and minimize sources of bias; * knows some leading authors and useful websites in the field of CLIL.
